<body>
         
      	<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam">
           
      	
      		<p><lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>svas</unclear>ti śrī</hi></p>
      		<p><unclear>vi</unclear>ramō<hi rend="grantha">ha</hi>ṉṉāṉa kāṭava
      			<lb break="no" n="2"/><unclear>r</unclear>āyaṉṉ aḻakiya-nampirāṭṭiyēṉ tiruppa</p>
      		<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
                     
      	</div>
         
      	<div type="apparatus">
           
               <listApp>
               	<app loc="2">
               		<lem>tiruppa</lem>
               		<rdg source="bib:Kuppusamy+Vijayavenugopal2006_01">tiruppa<unclear>ṇi</unclear></rdg>
               		<rdg source="bib:Vijayavenugopal2017_01">tiruppaṇi</rdg>
               		<note>The full word is most probably <foreign>tiruppaṇi</foreign>.</note> 
               	</app>
               	
               </listApp>         
      	</div>
      	
      	<div resp="part:vija" type="translation">
      		<p n="1">
      			Prosperity! Fortune! 
      		</p>
      		<p n="1-2">
      			Sacred service <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruppaṇi</foreign></supplied> of Aḻakiya-Nampirāṭṭi, <supplied reason="explanation">wife of</supplied> the Kāṭavarāyar alias Vīṟamōhaṉ
      			<gap reason="lost"/>
      		</p>
      		
      	</div>
      	
      	<div type="commentary">
      		<p>
      			Vīramohaṉ Kāṭavarāyaṉ may be Ēḻicaimohaṉ, the son of the Kāṭavarāya King Āṭkolliyār.
      		</p>
      		<p>
      			Since this inscription is found on the base of a small shrine, it may refer to the construction of this small shrine, as a service.
      		</p>
      	</div>
      	
